Alam Sutera, Aneka, Indofarma, Medco: Indonesia Equity Preview

-- B y   B e r n i   M o e s t a f a
-- 
2011-10-03T01:40:59Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-03/alam-sutera-aneka-indofarma-medco-indonesia-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies may
have unusual moves in Indonesian trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and share prices are as of the previous close.  The  Jakarta Composite index (JCI)  rose 0.3 percent to 3,549.03.  Energy companies: Crude oil fell as much as 1.6 percent to
$77.90 a barrel in after-hours trading in  New York , extending a
3.6 percent slump on Sept. 30.  PT Medco Energi Internasional (MEDC IJ),  Indonesia â€™s
biggest listed oil company, rose 1.2 percent to 2,150 rupiah and
PT Energi Mega Persada (ENRG IJ), the second largest, gained 3.7
percent to 132 rupiah.  PT Alam Sutera Realty (ASRI IJ): The property developer may
postpone plans to issue about 1.1 trillion rupiah ($122 million)
of dollar bonds this year due to market conditions, Bisnis
Indonesia reported, citing President Director Tri Ramadi. Alam
Sutera rose 4.1 percent to 385 rupiah.  PT Aneka Tambang (ANTM IJ): The nickel and gold producer
plans to sell 1.5 trillion rupiah to 2 trillion rupiah of bonds
in December,  Bisnis Indonesia  reported, citing Eddy Sugito, a
director at the Indonesia Stock Exchange. Aneka Corporate
Secretary Bimo Budi Satriyo confirmed the planned bond sale, the
report said. Aneka jumped 4.2 percent to 1,500 rupiah.  PT Kimia Farma (KAEF IJ): The state pharmaceutical producer
plans to sell a 30 percent stake in a rights offer of new shares
to raise about 500 billion rupiah in the first quarter of next
year, Kontan reported, citing President Director Muhammad
Sjamsul Arifin. Kimia Farma will use the funds to acquire state-
owned drug maker PT Indofarma (INAF IJ) and build two factories,
the report said. Kimia Farma was unchanged at 245 rupiah.
Indofarma was unchanged at 74 rupiah.  To contact the reporter on this story:
